    "note": "Drewery's Sock Dike, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Riston\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"en:Riston\">Riston</a>, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/East_Riding_of_Yorkshire\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"en:East Riding of Yorkshire\">East Riding of Yorkshire</a>, England.<br>Footpath Taken from the remote minor <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wawne\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"en:Wawne\">Wawne</a> to <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Skirlaugh\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"en:Skirlaugh\">Skirlaugh</a> road.  Haven't a clue why this drainage channel should have such a peculiar name!  On the right of the picture on the track can be seen the remnants of a burnt out car - an unfortunate product of 'modern' society."
